  "prompt": "Does Reliance JIO 4G require internet to make voice calls?",
  "response": "Yes, Reliance Jio uses Voice over LTE (VoLTE) technology for voice calls, which means that it transmits voice calls over the internet. Therefore, to make voice calls using Reliance Jio 4G, you will need an active internet connection. However, Jio's network is designed to ensure that voice calls can be made seamlessly as long as you have a good 4G signal. Jio does not require a separate voice plan, as the voice calls are included in the data package.",
